The year '''1573 in art''' involved some significant events and new works.
==Events== *[[July 18]] - [[Paolo Veronese]] is called before the [[Roman Catholic Inquisition]] to answer the charge of including irreverent matter in the large canvas of the [[Last Supper in Christian art|Last Supper]] he has just painted for the [[refectory]] of the [[Dominican order|Dominican]] basilica of [[Santi Giovanni e Paolo, Venice]] (to replace an earlier work by Titian destroyed in a fire in 1571). He responds by retitling it ''[[The Feast in the House of Levi]]''.
==Works== [[File:Banquet in the House of Levi by Paolo Veronese - Accademia - Venice 2016 (2).jpg|thumb|300px|[[Paolo Veronese|Veronese]] – ''[[The Feast in the House of Levi]]'', [[Gallerie dell'Accademia]]]] *[[Giuseppe Arcimboldo]] – ''Four Seasons'' series *[[Giambologna]] – ''[[Female Figure (Giambologna)|Female Figure]]'' (marble; approximate date) *[[Johan Gregor van der Schardt]] – ''Self-portrait'' (painted [[terracotta]] bust; approximate date)<ref>{{cite web|title=Jan Gregor van der Schardt|url=https://www.rijksmuseum.nl/en/explore-the-collection/overview/jan-gregor-van-der-schardt|publisher=[[Rijksmuseum]]|location=Amsterdam|accessdate=2012-12-06}}</ref> *[[Paolo Veronese]] **''[[Adoration of the Magi (Veronese)|Adoration of the Magi]]'' **''[[The Feast in the House of Levi]]'' **''The Martyrdom of St. Justine'' (possible date)
