{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Reporteri | logo = | image = | caption = | type = | format = | owners = | founder = | publisher = [[University of Tirana]] | president = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | generalmanager = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | metroeditor = | metrochief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{start date and age|1993|10|20|df=yes}} | political = | language = | ceased publication = | relaunched = | headquarters = [[Tirana]] | circulation = | circulation_date = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | RNI = | website = | free = | dirinteractive = }}
'''''Reporteri''''' is a student newspaper published in [[Tirana]], [[Albania]].
==History and profile== ''Reporteri'' which is published in [[Albanian language]] was established on 20 October 1993 as a monthly student newspaper published by those attending the department of journalism at the [[University of Tirana]].<ref name=osce/><ref name=dd>{{cite news|title=Media: Americans Teach Albania a Lesson in Free Press|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1994-05-10/news/wr-56082_1_press-law|accessdate=23 January 2014|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=10 May 1994|author=Denise Hamilton|location=Tirana}}</ref> Its foundation was supported by three [[US]] [[Graduate student|graduate]] [[journalism]] students from [[Columbia University]] who taught journalism at the University of Tirana.<ref name=dd/><ref name=nb>{{cite journal|title=Students try to promote free press in Albania|journal=Columbia Daily Spectator|date=15 September 1994|volume=CXVIII|issue=83|url=http://spectatorarchive.library.columbia.edu/cgi-bin/columbia?a=d&d=cs19940915-01.2.39&srpos=&e=-------en-20--1--txt-txIN------|accessdate=23 January 2014|author=Natacha Bodemann}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Governments Clamp Down on Freewheeling Media Also moved in advance|url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1993/Governments-Clamp-Down-on-Freewheeling-Media-Also-moved-in-advance-Dec-13-as-b0277-With-PM-Press-Glance/id-2499ca5239638bad71063ac31bc97708|accessdate=23 January 2014|work=Associated Press|date=20 December 1993|author=Alison Smale|location=Tirana}}</ref> In addition, its foundation was financially assisted by the [[IMF]] and the [[Soros Foundation]].<ref name=van>{{cite web|title=On the Road to a Free Press in Albania: Evaluating outside Aid Efforts|url=http://www.grady.uga.edu/coxcenter/Conference_Papers/Public_TCs/Free_Press_Albania.pdf|work=The University of Georgia|accessdate=23 January 2014|author=Van Kornegay|year=1995}}</ref> In the first issue the aim of ''Reporteri'' was stated as "to provide objective and balanced information, free of political or ideological taint."<ref name=nb/> The first [[editor-in-chief]] of the paper was Uliana Kociu.<ref name=nb/>
Following the publication of the first issue which featured issues like corruption, prostitution, smuggling, the position of minorities, the new tax system and pollution the paper was closed down by university authorities.<ref name=ijn>{{cite web|title=Journalism students in Albania get a taste of free reporting|url=http://ijnet.org/opportunities/journalism-students-albania-get-taste-free-reporting|work=International Journalists' Network|accessdate=23 January 2014|date=8 March 2000}}</ref><ref name=hrw>{{cite book|title=Human Rights in Post-communist Albania|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KfWxs-NdDhgC&pg=PA89|accessdate=23 January 2014|year=1996|publisher=Human Rights Watch|isbn=978-1-56432-160-2|page=110}}</ref> Later the paper was relaunched by the Soros Foundation<ref name=van/> and in the fall of 1995, it moved back to the university following the appointment of a new dean.<ref name=hrw/>
In March 2006, the paper became a fortnightly [[Supplement (publishing)|supplement]] to the Saturday edition of the now-defunct daily ''[[Korrieri]]'' through financial support of the [[Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe]].<ref name=osce>{{cite web|title=Tirana student newspaper goes nationwide with support from OSCE Presence in Albania|url=http://www.osce.org/albania/57501|work=OSCE|accessdate=23 January 2014|author1=Suela Shala|author2=Felipe Daza|date=13 June 2006}}</ref>
